<div class="c220_25"> 
<div id="v220.25.1"><span class="H6030 s">Then answered</span><span class="H1085 s"> Bildad</span><span class="H7747 s"> the Shuhite</span><span class="H559 s">, and said</span>,</div> 
<div id="v220.25.2"><span class="H4910 s">Dominion</span><span class="H6343 s"> and fear</span><span class="H6213 s"> <i>are</i> with him, he maketh</span><span class="H7965 s"> peace</span><span class="H4791 s"> in his high places</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.25.3"><span class="H3426 s">Is there</span><span class="H4557 s"> any number</span><span class="H1416 s"> of his armies</span><span class="H216 s">? and upon whom doth not his light</span><span class="H6965 s"> arise</span>?</div> 
<div id="v220.25.4"><span class="H582 s">How then can man</span><span class="H6663 s"> be justified</span><span class="H410 s"> with God</span><span class="H2135 s">? or how can he be clean</span><span class="H3205 s"> <i>that is</i> born</span><span class="H802 s"> of a woman</span>?</div> 
<div id="v220.25.5"><span class="H3394 s">Behold even to the moon</span><span class="H166 s">, and it shineth</span><span class="H3556 s"> not; yea, the stars</span><span class="H2141 s"> are not pure</span><span class="H5869 s"> in his sight</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.25.6"><span class="H582 s">How much less man</span><span class="H7415 s">, <i>that is</i> a worm</span><span class="H1121 s">? and the son</span><span class="H120 s"> of man</span><span class="H8438 s">, <i>which is</i> a worm</span>?</div></div> 
